//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_lode_augur}

NOTE: This operation inspects a single
{rbtga_lode}
— listing its member tags and decoding its
{rbtga_lode_vouch}
provenance envelope — by querying GAR directly via the Registry API.
Read-only; no local container runtime.
Authenticates as
{rbtr_director}.

NOTE: Augur is the single-Lode inspect verb — the perceiving counterpart, at member grain, to
{rbtgo_lode_divine}'s
lifecycle-grain enumeration.
Divine answers which Lodes exist; augur answers what is inside one — its member tags and its decoded
{rbtga_lode_vouch}
envelope.
The fetched-side parallel of made-side
{rbtgo_ark_inspect}.

NOTE: Augur is kind-agnostic.
It decodes the kind from the
{rbtga_touchmark}
leading letter and reads the same-shaped envelope every kind carries — so a new Lode kind needs no change here.

The
{rbtr_director}
augurs a Lode:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_touchmark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«TOUCHMARK»` provided as the operation folio
.. {rbbc_require}
`«TOUCHMARK»` matches the touchmark format `«KIND»YYMMDDHHMMSS` (see
{rbst_touchmark})
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Touchmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Fetch Member Tags*:
.. {rbbc_call}
GAR REST `tags.list` for the Lode package `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»`
.. {rbbc_require}
at least one tag present — an empty package is the "Lode not present" signal
.. {rbbc_store}
`«MEMBER_TAGS»` — every member tag on the package

//axhos_step
. *Decode Provenance Envelope*:
.. {rbbc_call}
Registry API: extract the `:rbi_vouch` manifest from the `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»` package and read its `vouch.json` layer
.. {rbbc_store}
the
{rbtga_lode_vouch}
fields: `kind`, `acquired_at`, `acquired_by`, `capture_build`, `trust_grade`, and `members[]` (each `origin` / `digest` / `verification` / `tags`)

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_lode}
. *Display*:
.. {rbbc_show}
the kind (decoded from the touchmark prefix), the member tags, and the decoded provenance — origin, canonical digest, trust grade, and acquisition facts
.. {rbbc_show}
explicit trust-grade posture: `verified-against-published` versus `recorded-at-acquisition`, so the displayed claim never over-states what the upstream permits

//axhoc_completion
Augur is a read-only inspection of one
{rbtga_lode}
via the GAR Registry API: it lists the member tags and decodes the
{rbtga_lode_vouch}
envelope, and modifies nothing.
+
The categorical layout makes the touchmark the primary index — every member tag and the provenance envelope sit within the one `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»` package, so no cross-Lode aggregator is needed.
+
Trust posture is reported honestly per the envelope's declared grade: a `recorded-at-acquisition` Lode states that RB attests only the digest observed at capture, never that it remains re-checkable against a vanished upstream.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_lode_divine}

NOTE: This operation enumerates every
{rbtga_lode}
under the
{gar_lodes_namespace}
namespace — one row per Lode, keyed by
{rbtga_touchmark},
with the Lode's unsprued glance fingerprint as the IMAGE column.
Read-only.

NOTE: Divine is kind-agnostic.
A touchmark's leading letter is its kind (`b260602...` is bole); divine prints a kind legend once and decodes each row's kind from the prefix, so a new Lode kind needs no change here.
Divine is lifecycle-grain — it enumerates Lodes by touchmark.
The per-Lode inspect depth — member tags and the
{rbtga_lode_vouch}
envelope — belongs to
{rbtgo_lode_augur},
not here.

The
{rbtr_director}
divines the Lodes:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. {rbbc_require}
Director credential file present
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *List Lode Packages*:
.. {rbbc_call}
GAR REST `packages.list` scoped to the
{gar_lodes_namespace}
root
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TOUCHMARKS»` — the package basenames under the namespace
.. If empty: {rbbc_show}
"0 Lodes" and complete — an empty namespace is not an error

//axhos_step
. *Print Kind Legend*:
.. {rbbc_show}
one row per Lode kind — e.g. `b  bole  upstream OCI image, consumed as a FROM line` — so each data row carries no repeated per-row kind column

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Each Lode's Fingerprint*:
.. For each `«TOUCHMARK»` in `«TOUCHMARKS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
GAR REST `tags.list` for the Lode package `{gar_lodes_namespace}/«TOUCHMARK»`
... {rbbc_store}
`«SHA10»` as the first 10 hex chars of the `:rbi_sha256-«HEX»` member tag
... {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE»` as the unsprued fingerprint tag ending in `-«SHA10»` (or `(no fingerprint)` when absent) — located via the digest-derived sha10 so a Director semantic name cannot masquerade as the fingerprint

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_lode}
. *Display Roster*:
.. {rbbc_show}
a `TOUCHMARK | IMAGE` table, one row per Lode
.. {rbbc_show}
total Lode count

//axhoc_completion
Divine is a read-only enumeration over the
{gar_lodes_namespace}
namespace: it lists every
{rbtga_lode}
by
{rbtga_touchmark}
with a glance fingerprint, and modifies nothing.
+
The kind legend plus prefix-decoding keeps divine kind-agnostic — adding a Lode kind adds a legend row, not a code path.
Per-Lode member and
{rbtga_lode_vouch}
detail is the inspect depth of
{rbtgo_lode_augur},
a distinct read-only operation in the same lifecycle family.

