### 2. How a Theurge Case Invokes a Tabtarget Colophon

#### **Invocation Mechanism** (from rbtdri_invocation.rs)

```rust
pub fn rbtdri_invoke_global(
    ctx: &mut rbtdri_Context,
    colophon: &str,
    args: &[&str],
    extra_env: &[(&str, &str)],
) -> Result<rbtdri_InvokeResult, String> {
    let tabtarget = rbtdri_find_tabtarget_global(&ctx.project_root, colophon)?;
    rbtdri_invoke_impl(ctx, &tabtarget, args, extra_env)
}
```

#### **Result Structure** (rbtdri_InvokeResult)

```rust
pub struct rbtdri_InvokeResult {
    pub stdout: String,
    pub stderr: String,
    pub exit_code: i32,
    pub burv_output: PathBuf,
}
```

#### **Representative End-to-End Example** (from reliquary_lifecycle, lines 3334-3346):

```rust
// CHARGE PHASE: invoke the colophon
let conclave = match rbtdri_invoke_global(ctx, RBTDGC_CONCLAVE_RELIQUARY, &[], &[]) {
    Ok(r) if r.exit_code == 0 => r,
