### 3. Lifecycle Fixture Structure (Case Registration & Definition)

#### **Case Registration Pattern**

```rust
pub static RBTDRC_CASES_LODE_LIFECYCLE: &[rbtdre_Case] = &[
    case!(rbtdrc_lode_lifecycle),
    case!(rbtdrc_lode_collision),
];

pub static RBTDRC_CASES_RELIQUARY_LIFECYCLE: &[rbtdre_Case] = &[case!(rbtdrc_reliquary_lifecycle)];

pub static RBTDRC_CASES_WSL_LIFECYCLE: &[rbtdre_Case] = &[case!(rbtdrc_wsl_lifecycle)];
```

The `case!()` macro expands to:
```rust
rbtdre_Case {
    name: stringify!($func),  // e.g., "rbtdrc_lode_lifecycle"
    func: $func,              // function pointer
}
```

#### **Case Function Signature**

All fixture cases follow this pattern:
```rust
fn rbtdrc_<lifecycle_name>(dir: &Path) -> rbtdre_Verdict {
    rbtdrc_with_ctx(|ctx| {
        // Test body: invoke colophons via ctx, assert on output
        // Returns rbtdre_Verdict::Pass or rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(String)
    })
}
```

The `rbtdrc_with_ctx()` closure wraps access to thread-local `rbtdri_Context` (set before test runs, providing access to project root and invocation state).

#### **Charge/Run/Assert Flow** (from lode_lifecycle):

```rust
fn rbtdrc_lode_lifecycle(dir: &Path) -> rbtdre_Verdict {
    rbtdrc_with_ctx(|ctx| {
        // STEP 1: CHARGE — Create fixture state
        let _ = std::fs::write(dir.join("01-ensconce.txt"), "ensconcing busybox base");
        let ensconce = match rbtdri_invoke_global(ctx, RBTDGC_ENSCONCE_BOLE, &[vessel_dir], &[]) {
            Ok(r) if r.exit_code == 0 => r,
            Ok(r) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("ensconce failed (exit {})\n{}", r.exit_code, r.stderr)),
            Err(e) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("ensconce invocation: {}", e)),
        };
        let _ = std::fs::write(dir.join("01-ensconce-stdout.txt"), &ensconce.stdout);

        // STEP 2: RUN — Extract key facts and invoke verification steps
        let touchmark = match rbtdri_read_burv_fact(&ensconce, RBTDRC_FACT_LODE_TOUCHMARK) {
            Ok(v) => v,
            Err(e) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("read touchmark fact: {}", e)),
        };

        // STEP 3+: ASSERT — Verify state across multiple invocations
        let after = match rbtdri_invoke_global(ctx, RBTDGC_DIVINE_LODES, &[], &[]) {
            // ... error handling ...
        };
        if !after.stdout.contains(&touchmark) {
            return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!(
                "post-ensconce divine missing touchmark {}\nstdout:\n{}",
                touchmark, after.stdout
            ));
        }

        let inspect = match rbtdri_invoke_global(ctx, RBTDGC_DIVINE_LODES, &[&touchmark], &[]) {
            // ... error handling ...
        };
        for member in &[RBTDRC_LODE_TAG_BOLE, RBTDRC_LODE_TAG_VOUCH, RBTDRC_LODE_TAG_DIGEST_PREFIX] {
            if !inspect.stdout.contains(member) {
                return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!(
                    "divine inspect missing member tag '{}'\nstdout:\n{}",
                    member, inspect.stdout
                ));
            }
        }

        // FINAL: Return verdict
        let _ = std::fs::write(dir.join("08-passed.txt"), "passed");
        rbtdre_Verdict::Pass
    })
}
```

#### **Adding a New Augur Case**

To add a new augur assertion case, create a new test function and register it in the case array:

```rust
// NEW CASE FUNCTION (e.g., to be added to reliquary_lifecycle)
fn rbtdrc_reliquary_augur_decode(dir: &Path) -> rbtdre_Verdict {
    rbtdrc_with_ctx(|ctx| {
        // Same conclave/touchmark setup as reliquary_lifecycle
        let conclave = match rbtdri_invoke_global(ctx, RBTDGC_CONCLAVE_RELIQUARY, &[], &[]) {
            Ok(r) if r.exit_code == 0 => r,
            Ok(r) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("conclave failed (exit {})\n{}", r.exit_code, r.stderr)),
            Err(e) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("conclave invocation: {}", e)),
        };
        let touchmark = match rbtdri_read_burv_fact(&conclave, RBTDRC_FACT_LODE_TOUCHMARK) {
            Ok(v) => v,
            Err(e) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("read touchmark fact: {}", e)),
        };

        // NEW: Invoke augur to decode :rbi_vouch envelope
        let augur = match rbtdri_invoke_global(ctx, RBTDGC_AUGUR_LODES, &[&touchmark], &[]) {
            Ok(r) if r.exit_code == 0 => r,
            Ok(r) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("augur decode failed (exit {})\n{}", r.exit_code, r.stderr)),
            Err(e) => return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!("augur decode invocation: {}", e)),
        };
        let _ = std::fs::write(dir.join("augur-decode.txt"), &augur.stdout);

        // ASSERT: augur decodes :rbi_vouch envelope with origin, digest, trust grade, acquisition facts
        for field in &["origin", "digest", "trust", "acquired"] {
            if !augur.stdout.contains(field) {
                return rbtdre_Verdict::Fail(format!(
                    "augur decode missing field '{}'\nstdout:\n{}",
                    field, augur.stdout
                ));
            }
        }

        let _ = std::fs::write(dir.join("augur-passed.txt"), "passed");
        rbtdre_Verdict::Pass
    })
}

// REGISTER NEW CASE in the array
pub static RBTDRC_CASES_RELIQUARY_LIFECYCLE: &[rbtdre_Case] = &[
    case!(rbtdrc_reliquary_lifecycle),
    case!(rbtdrc_reliquary_augur_decode),  // ← NEW CASE
];
```

---

### 4. Colophon Constants Pattern

#### **Constant Location & Format**
- **File**: `/Users/bhyslop/projects/rbm_alpha_recipemuster/Tools/rbk/rbtd/src/rbtdgc_consts.rs`
- **Note**: Auto-generated by theurge build (`tt/rbw-tb.Build.sh` per header comment)
- **Format**: `pub const RBTDGC_<VERB>_<OBJECT>: &str = "rbw-<code>";`

#### **Current Divine Constant** (line 36):

```rust
pub const RBTDGC_DIVINE_LODES: &str = "rbw-ld";
```

#### **Where Augur Will Appear (Post-Zipper Regeneration)**

Based on the naming pattern, augur (the new inspect verb) will likely be:

```rust
pub const RBTDGC_AUGUR_LODES: &str = "rbw-la";
```

This follows the pattern:
- Prefix: `rbw-` (all colophons)
- Subsystem code: `l` (Lodes, matching divine `ld`)
- Verb code: `a` (augur, following `d` for divine alphabetically)

#### **How to Use in Tests** (post-constant generation)

Once the constant is generated and imported at the top of `rbtdrc_crucible.rs`:

```rust
